data.enText: relating to the examination and treatment of patients and their illnesses
clinical research (= done on patients, not just considering theory)
clinical training (= the part of a doctor's training done in a hospital)

data.chText: 冷淡的；无动于衷的；无同情心的
data.enText: cold and calm and without feeling or sympathy

data.chText: 他无动于衷地看着她受苦。
data.enText: He watched her suffering with clinical detachment.

data.chText: 临床死亡的（从身体的状况判断为死亡的）
data.enText: clinically dead (= judged to be dead from the condition of the body)

example: he spoke in the clipped clinical monotones typical of police testimony

tr: relating to a clinic or conducted in or as if in a clinic and depending on direct observation of patients

value.def: Clinical means involving or relating to the direct medical treatment or testing of patients.

example.ex: The first clinical trials were expected to begin next year.
example.tran: 第一批临床实验有望明年开始。

example.ex: She was diagnosed as being clinically depressed...
example.tran: 她被临床诊断为患有抑郁症。

example.ex: It has been clinically proved that it is better to stretch the tight muscles first.
example.tran: 经临床证明，最好先放松紧张的肌肉。

value.def: You use clinical to describe thought or behaviour which is very logical and does not involve any emotion.

example.ex: All this questioning is so analytical and clinical — it kills romance.
example.tran: 整个询问分析性和逻辑性太强，浪漫的气息荡然无存。

value.tran: （思想、行为）非常符合逻辑的，不带感情的
